情人节快到，还不知道去哪儿和专属的Ta或者你的好基友们一起过？小编建议：如果你在以下地图中的这些城市，不如就去这些LGBTQ+友好的商家吧~安全友善的空间，开放热心的店家，为自己制造一份专属浪漫~

Valentine's Day is coming, still do not know where to go with your special one or your BFFs? Here is my advice: If you are in one of the cities as shown on the map below, check out these LGBTQ+ friendly safe spaces~ Safe & friendly environment, open-minded & warm-hearted owners. I'm sure it is gonna be an awesome experience~



友善空间地图

Safe Space Map



LGBTQ+ （拉拉，gay，双性恋，跨性别者及酷儿等）是这个世界上人群中的性少数，Ta们因为自身性别及性取向的不同而不能被很多人认同，不能像大多数人一样自由地表达爱和自己。友善空间地图项目旨在为LGBTQ+人群发掘更多友好空间（餐馆，酒吧，咖啡馆，发廊等等），让Ta们更能感受到整个城市的善意与温暖。同时，通过地图的拓展，也让更多大众意识到LGBTQ+人群的存在，起到倡导与教育的作用，进而可以理解Ta们。该项目从2015年6月于浙江宁波市发起，到现在已经发展到14座城市，超过250个商家。历经3个月，跨越7个城市，经过她她公益和7个地方LGBTQ+小组的共同努力，新版友善空间地图终于随着2017新年一同到来......

LGBTQ+ people are still not fully accepted because of their different gender identity or different sexual orientation. Hence they are likely to conceal their feelings about love and the most authentic selves. The safe space map is mainly aimed at exploring more LGBTQ+ friendly spaces (like restaurants, bars, cafe……). Through collecting more and more these places we can make sexual and gender minorities feel the warmth and kindness of the whole city. At the same times, the public can also be more aware of LGBTQ+ people and then learn to embrace the diversity of individuals. Started from Ningbo Zhejiang, this project has managed to take off in 15 cities & provinces and there are about 250 places on the map. We are still working on the map. If you can provide more places, welcome to join us.


先来看下我们部分商家的图片咯~很多商家情人节会有一些特惠活动或Party~正好有了当天晚上可供消遣的好去处~

Have a look at the pictures of the partial safe spaces~many of them will provide special offers or even party events in Valentine's Day~

上海 | Shanghai


Ronglek (平武路29号）

为单身的你准备的情人节party，Gabby携LQ邀请你来与我们分享你过去的故事

无论你在哪个城市，无论你是直人还是LGBTQ+，无论你是商家，个人还是团队，我们都欢迎你加入寻找友善商家的行列中去~让我们点亮更多爱的星光，星星点点，汇成海洋~我们友善空间地图项目会一直持续下去，欢迎各位推荐友好商家，或者与我们一起合作参与到项目中去。

No matter who you are, which city you are in, we all welcome you to join the Safe Space Map Project. Let's work together, then finally we will create a more tolerant and equal environment for LGBTQ+ people.
